parameters:
Thief Nora: Achoo! It's cold up here in the sky... I didn't
know that.

Researcher Caron: We are able to maintain a stable state,
but I don't think the crystals and magicians can handle it
as much as I thought.

Noble Kasaro: In just a short time, it should be dawn before
we know it...

Researcher Caron: I will go back inside. Everyone, please
come inside when you find the right timing.

Noble Kasaro: Thank you all so much. It's thanks to everyone
that we were able to come this far.

Clea: I heard that Kasaro-san was about to enter the Senate
soon.

Clea: Why did you abandon everything to chase after this
dream?

Noble Kasaro: Both my father and grandfather dreamed of
entering the Senate, so naturally, I, who was raised with
that background, pursued the same dream.

Noble Kasaro: For that reason, I wished for my son, who
built the bathhouse and even participated in wars, to have
the same dream...

Noble Kasaro: When I heard that I would be participating in
the naval battle with Tarasa, I didn't hesitate to see it as
a natural step towards becoming a senator.

Priestess Sophia: The naval battle with Tarasa... It was the
battle with the highest number of casualties in the Second
Tarasa War, wasn't it?

Noble Kasaro: When I heard the report of my son's death, I
foolishly considered how I could use his death to my
advantage.

Noble Kasaro: Having a father like me, my son must have been
unhappy. A few months after receiving the report of his
death in battle, I received a letter from my son.

Noble Kasaro: I want to see the place where the sea, which
should be a terrifying battlefield, looks beautiful and
shines with the blue color that my father loves, together
someday...

Noble Kasaro: I don't know anything about what he liked...
We lived together, we lived together, and yet he knew!

Noble Kasaro: That's why he came here, to see the place
where the beautiful sky and sea overlap...\|...\|
